Grain SA Says JSE Transport Price Adjustment May Cost Farmers $68 Million

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-04-08T11:15:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/grain-sa-says-jse-transport-price-adjustment-may-cost-farmers-68-million.html
Grain SA, the South African farmers’
group, said a change made in the Johannesburg stock exchange’s
calculation of corn transport costs may cost producers as much
as 451 million rand.  The new “location differentials” will have a “dramatic
effect” on the price that corn producers can negotiate for
their grain, Grain SA said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  